<h3>Email Copy Best Practices</h3>
<p>Write the way you speak. Contractors are not marketing agencies. Your customers prefer straightforward language over polished corporate speak.</p>
<p>Keep paragraphs short. 2-3 sentences maximum. Use bullet points for lists. Include one clear call to action per email, not 5.</p>
<p>Every email should answer one question: "What do you want the reader to do next?" If the answer is not obvious, rewrite the email.</p>
